{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f3dd300-fb9b-4d06-bb1f-c5682b5124c8","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **test ID generation strategy** from `DisplayName` to `FullyQualifiedName`. Azure DevOps tracks tests by ID, so every test looks new.\n\n**Fix** — add this to your `.csproj` (or `.runsettings`):\n\n```xml\n<TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n```","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0155UVAKqVyEtt17G1AvcahA","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-eb5410f605f7433ea36ba752993706b0/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-eb5410f605f7433ea36ba752993706b0/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"70626ae0-0505-43bf-939d-a557ce5ebe1d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 breaking changes. Let me provide a comprehensive answer based on what I know about MSTest v4 changes.\n\nKey MSTest v4 breaking changes:\n\n1. **Fully qualified test ID** — MSTest v4 changed the default test ID format to use fully qualified names (namespace + class + method). This is why Azure DevOps sees all tests as \"new\" with no history. The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>` in the project file or a `.runsettings` file to restore the old behavior.\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** — In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a *class-level* context, not tied to any specific test. Accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws `NotSupportedException` because there's no test running yet at class-init time. This is a deliberate change to make the semantics more correct.\n   \n3. Beyond these two major shifts, there are several other areas where v4 diverges from earlier versions: `[DeploymentItem]` attributes behave differently, `TestContext.Properties` became read-only in certain scenarios, parallel execution settings shifted their defaults, and the timing of assembly and class cleanup methods changed. Additionally, how the `DataRow` attribute works has been modified.","outputTokens":642,"requestId":"CFCB:B0AF0:620CBDA:6E4EEF0:69EC2BDE"},"id":"4dabab2c-8fbc-4f72-8b5e-acf61f48f19b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:50:18.327Z","parentId":"3570d384-546a-4d10-b625-0cf64634a0c9"}
