{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c67f4402-e542-4cc2-8ac1-b4da59b5edd6","content":"---\n\n### 3. Other v4 things to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Cleanup timing** | `[ClassCleanup]` now defaults to `EndOfClass` (was `EndOfAssembly`). Same for `[AssemblyCleanup]` ordering. |\n| **Parallel execution** | Parallelism defaults may differ; verify your `[Parallelize]` / `.runsettings` settings. |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | Now read-only in class/assembly init contexts. |\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Stricter type matching — implicit conversions that worked in v3 may now fail. |\n| **`Assert.ThrowsException`** | No longer catches derived exception types by default; use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` or check docs. |\n| **Removed APIs** | Some long-deprecated members were removed. Build will catch these. |\n\nThe two fixes above (restoring `DisplayName` IDs and removing `TestName` from class init) should resolve your immediate issues.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"70626ae0-0505-43bf-939d-a557ce5ebe1d","outputTokens":259,"requestId":"CFCB:B0AF0:620F1DF:6E51F00:69EC2BEF"},"id":"33e014ea-0594-4283-8e14-b1dd0aa24848","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:50:31.127Z","parentId":"30d2b456-6c5b-407a-a3d5-d06cc17e664c"}
